Class PuzzleConfiguration

  • java.lang.Object
    • PuzzleConfiguration

  • public class PuzzleConfiguration
extends java.lang.Object
    PuzzleConfiguration is a class which represents a single state of a Puzzle It is initialised by using strings which are parsed and validated appropriately It can generate the possible configurations that it can go to Created by Toby Leheup on 28/02/14.
    Version:
    28/02/2014
    Author:
    Toby Leheup - TL258

      • generateNextConfigs

        public java.util.List<PuzzleConfiguration> generateNextConfigs()
        Generates the next possible configurations from this configuration A configuration can move left, right, up or down only. Any move can only be performed if there is a valid cell in the place that _ wants to move to
        Returns:
        A list of configurations that can be moved to from base

      • generateMoveUp

        public PuzzleConfiguration generateMoveUp()
        Generates a new configuration where the '_' character in the current configuration has swapped with the character above it. If this is not possible, the '_' character remains where it is
        Returns:
        Either the new configuration or null if '_' cannot move
